cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with characterizing compute kernel execution behavior on GPUs for efficient task scheduling, which falls under the category of performance analysis and optimization. Therefore, cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.PF (Performance) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses power consumption, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of machine learning for prediction could also place this paper under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
